{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-knowledge-base-template-js","path":"/robots/motor-controller-board","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Observation: everyone creates their version [of motor controller/driver board]</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.thea.codes/starfish-a-control-board-with-the-rp2040/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Starfish</a> by Stargirl</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/TLAlexander/status/1720693291069689897\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Acorn</a> by Taylor Alexander</li>\n</ul>\n<p>or relies on currently available shields or hats</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Pimoroni Yukon board</li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"flex:0.7511520737327189;\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/38cf2d27fadc3ce5a708235b6cf9f10b/ac99c/pimoroni_yukon.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.12883435582822%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Yukon driver board\"\n        title=\"Photo by [Dr Footleg](https://twitter.com/drfootleg)\"\n        src=\"/static/38cf2d27fadc3ce5a708235b6cf9f10b/6aca1/pimoroni_yukon.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/38cf2d27fadc3ce5a708235b6cf9f10b/d2f63/pimoroni_yukon.jpg 163w,\n/static/38cf2d27fadc3ce5a708235b6cf9f10b/c989d/pimoroni_yukon.jpg 325w,\n/static/38cf2d27fadc3ce5a708235b6cf9f10b/6aca1/pimoroni_yukon.jpg 650w,\n/static/38cf2d27fadc3ce5a708235b6cf9f10b/7c09c/pimoroni_yukon.jpg 975w,\n/static/38cf2d27fadc3ce5a708235b6cf9f10b/01ab0/pimoroni_yukon.jpg 1300w,\n/static/38cf2d27fadc3ce5a708235b6cf9f10b/ac99c/pimoroni_yukon.jpg 1536w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Photo by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/drfootleg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Dr Footleg</a></p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Maybe that's why Yukon is very popular, but why not to make this customly expandable? Should I think about RP2040 Yukon clone but with something different from Cortex M0</p>\n<h2 id=\"h-bridge\" style=\"position:relative;\">H-Bridge<a href=\"#h-bridge\" aria-label=\"h bridge permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>H-bridge, also called as <em>full bridge</em> (but not half bridge), is a motor driver that allows the motor to rotate forward and backward. With independent movement of every wheel we will implement <em>skid-steer drive</em>. H-Bridge can be created with the help of four MOSFETs and diodes.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Unwise to power an H-bridge with two d-a's, forward and reverse, you run risk of powering both sides on at once. This destroys the H-bridge and can destroy the motor. Be really careful. You can only power one at a time.</p>\n<p><em>Tony about homemade H-Bridge implementation</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Or it can be an IC. I looked into this <a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/product/2448\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">breakout board</a> based on classic <a href=\"https://cdn-shop.adafruit.com/datasheets/TB6612FNG_datasheet_en_20121101.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">TB6612</a> that supports 2 motors and 1.2A per channel.\nOther super classic options will be <strong>L293D</strong> and <strong>L298</strong>.</p>\n<p>So why not to use classic bridges like L298N, or L293D, or TB6612? Because they cost $12 per chip, and they are out of stock üò≠</p>\n<p>Next, I check what chips are available at the moment. Texas Instruments offers</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.mouser.com/ProductDetail/595-DRV8210DSGR\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">DRV8210</a> 1 channel <a href=\"https://www.ti.com/general/docs/suppproductinfo.tsp?distId=26&#x26;gotoUrl=https://www.ti.com/lit/gpn/drv8210\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">1.76A</a> or</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.digikey.com/en/products/detail/texas-instruments/DRV8836DSSR/3088190\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">DRV8836</a> 2 channels <a href=\"https://www.ti.com/general/docs/suppproductinfo.tsp?distId=10&#x26;gotoUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ti.com%2Flit%2Fgpn%2Fdrv8836\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">1.5A</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I had a gut feeling that I didn‚Äôt check all specs for my H-Bridges. I stopped my choice on</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>DRV8836</strong> Dual Low-Voltage H-Bridge IC from Texas Instruments and</li>\n<li><strong>A3909</strong> Dual Full Bridge Motor Driver from Allegro Microsystems</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I was checking <strong>level input voltage</strong>, how many motors it can drive (checking the type of connection that is different for DC motor, bipolar DC motor, and stepper motor), and was comparing <strong>stall motor current</strong> with <strong>maximum output current</strong>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"speed-control\" style=\"position:relative;\">Speed control<a href=\"#speed-control\" aria-label=\"speed control permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>First I started worrying what kind of input is required. UART, I2C protocol, PWM signal? How to implement speed control? Do I need Digital-to-analog converter?</p>\n<p>My friend Tony asked his engineer the same questions and he <a href=\"/make/robot/letter-from-the-engineer\">raised many questions</a> about the design, ADC and precautions against H-Bridge.</p>\n<p>Let's think. It‚Äôs not a stepper motor, therefore we don‚Äôt need to send pulses, just ON or OFF signals. PWM might produce different speed. I need to check how many PWM outputs on ATMega chips. But the question is: is it possible to simulate PWM on regular DOUT?</p>\n<h2 id=\"dual-channel\" style=\"position:relative;\">Dual channel<a href=\"#dual-channel\" aria-label=\"dual channel permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Guess how I was surprised today that <em>Dual Full Bridge</em> means that the second motor is moving exactly as the first one. And we are talking about bipolar DC motors. Yes, it‚Äôs not another independent channel. IT IS NOT.</p>\n<p>Looking at TI's DRV8210 and Toshiba's <a href=\"https://toshiba.semicon-storage.com/info/TC78H660FTG_datasheet_en_20200714.pdf?did=68604&#x26;prodName=TC78H660FTG\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">TC78H660FTG</a> now üòã Another alternative can be <a href=\"https://www.mouser.com/datasheet/2/256/TMC7300_Datasheet_V105-2066925.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">TMC7300</a> that includes DC converter and can work from the battery directly.</p>\n<p><strong>How to verify it?</strong> Datasheets should include a control table - output levels corresponding to input signals. Here's for example <strong>A3909</strong> that disappointed me (DC Motor section, INs are merged - not independent)</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; flex:1.1398601398601398;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b7de7a7b1fcdcc55f5e9c33d432ba2aa/75609/motor-driver-datasheet-a3909.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 87.73006134969326%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Datasheet for A3909\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/b7de7a7b1fcdcc55f5e9c33d432ba2aa/a6d36/motor-driver-datasheet-a3909.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b7de7a7b1fcdcc55f5e9c33d432ba2aa/222b7/motor-driver-datasheet-a3909.png 163w,\n/static/b7de7a7b1fcdcc55f5e9c33d432ba2aa/ff46a/motor-driver-datasheet-a3909.png 325w,\n/static/b7de7a7b1fcdcc55f5e9c33d432ba2aa/a6d36/motor-driver-datasheet-a3909.png 650w,\n/static/b7de7a7b1fcdcc55f5e9c33d432ba2aa/e548f/motor-driver-datasheet-a3909.png 975w,\n/static/b7de7a7b1fcdcc55f5e9c33d432ba2aa/75609/motor-driver-datasheet-a3909.png 994w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>For <strong>DRV8836</strong> we will see completely different picture. There one small table that works for both channels (1 and 2) and marked as 'x'</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; flex:2.08974358974359;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7621f2c3f0cc20ee605b3b8deae982eb/2e195/motor-driver-datasheet-drv8836.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 47.852760736196316%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Datasheet for DRV8836\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/7621f2c3f0cc20ee605b3b8deae982eb/a6d36/motor-driver-datasheet-drv8836.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7621f2c3f0cc20ee605b3b8deae982eb/222b7/motor-driver-datasheet-drv8836.png 163w,\n/static/7621f2c3f0cc20ee605b3b8deae982eb/ff46a/motor-driver-datasheet-drv8836.png 325w,\n/static/7621f2c3f0cc20ee605b3b8deae982eb/a6d36/motor-driver-datasheet-drv8836.png 650w,\n/static/7621f2c3f0cc20ee605b3b8deae982eb/2e195/motor-driver-datasheet-drv8836.png 782w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>And compare both previous tables with this clear table and extra notes from Toshiba <strong>TC78H660FTG</strong> üòç</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; flex:1.044871794871795;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1a0692a412d388d44de796a1fd50d69a/914ae/motor-driver-datasheet-tc78h660ftg.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 95.70552147239263%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Datasheet for TC78H660FTG\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/1a0692a412d388d44de796a1fd50d69a/a6d36/motor-driver-datasheet-tc78h660ftg.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1a0692a412d388d44de796a1fd50d69a/222b7/motor-driver-datasheet-tc78h660ftg.png 163w,\n/static/1a0692a412d388d44de796a1fd50d69a/ff46a/motor-driver-datasheet-tc78h660ftg.png 325w,\n/static/1a0692a412d388d44de796a1fd50d69a/a6d36/motor-driver-datasheet-tc78h660ftg.png 650w,\n/static/1a0692a412d388d44de796a1fd50d69a/914ae/motor-driver-datasheet-tc78h660ftg.png 860w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"schematics\" style=\"position:relative;\">Schematics<a href=\"#schematics\" aria-label=\"schematics permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"full-bridge-driving-typical-application\" style=\"position:relative;\">Full-Bridge driving typical application<a href=\"#full-bridge-driving-typical-application\" aria-label=\"full bridge driving typical application permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"flex:2.232876712328767;\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/71fe5b9dc1ff2133e68a38c0305064a2/8f5d7/h-bridge-typical-application-drv8210.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 44.78527607361963%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Full-Bridge driving typical application\"\n        title=\"PWM interface motor-driving application for DSG package\"\n        src=\"/static/71fe5b9dc1ff2133e68a38c0305064a2/a6d36/h-bridge-typical-application-drv8210.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/71fe5b9dc1ff2133e68a38c0305064a2/222b7/h-bridge-typical-application-drv8210.png 163w,\n/static/71fe5b9dc1ff2133e68a38c0305064a2/ff46a/h-bridge-typical-application-drv8210.png 325w,\n/static/71fe5b9dc1ff2133e68a38c0305064a2/a6d36/h-bridge-typical-application-drv8210.png 650w,\n/static/71fe5b9dc1ff2133e68a38c0305064a2/e548f/h-bridge-typical-application-drv8210.png 975w,\n/static/71fe5b9dc1ff2133e68a38c0305064a2/3c492/h-bridge-typical-application-drv8210.png 1300w,\n/static/71fe5b9dc1ff2133e68a38c0305064a2/8f5d7/h-bridge-typical-application-drv8210.png 1475w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>PWM interface motor-driving application for DSG package</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Note: Pay attention to a paragraph about bulk resistance</p>\n<p><strong>Additional components</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1x capacitors <a href=\"https://www.mouser.com/ProductDetail/81-GRM188R60J106ME4D\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">10uF</a> - voltage Rating 6.3VDC</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"alternative-boards\" style=\"position:relative;\">Alternative boards<a href=\"#alternative-boards\" aria-label=\"alternative boards permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"flex:1.4051724137931034;\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9f6da5ef6206477765e45c6ab463aca4/bb072/Arduino-shield-L293D-bird-tokyo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 71.16564417177914%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Arduino shield\"\n        title=\"Credit: @bird_tokyo\"\n        src=\"/static/9f6da5ef6206477765e45c6ab463aca4/a6d36/Arduino-shield-L293D-bird-tokyo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9f6da5ef6206477765e45c6ab463aca4/222b7/Arduino-shield-L293D-bird-tokyo.png 163w,\n/static/9f6da5e